<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880111-0054 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: National Business Systems Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> NBSIF </CO><IN> BBK </IN><TEXT>   National Business Systems Inc., Toronto, said it intends to purchase about 19% of its shares outstanding for 14.50 Canadian dollars each, or 43.5 million dollars ($33.8 million).    The maker of plastic transaction cards and related equipment said it intends to offer to buy back three million shares through the facilities of the Toronto Stock Exchange. Dominion Securities Inc. has been retained as the company's agent.    In trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange Friday, National Business shares closed at 12.625 dollars, up 25 cents. </TEXT></DOC>